Give yourself permission to slow down. 

Practice patience and pay attention to what the body and the heart or guts are telling you. 

When we go too fast we can miss important signals. Love your body and be kind with your thoughts.There are a lot of nuggets out on the mat. Stay present and enjoy! 

Use a blanket today to lift the hips! Also, there might be some massage at the end of this practice. YAY.

For a few days I’ve felt a bit off and I couldn’t seem to figure out why.
I’ve been clenching some places but I didn’t notice where exactly.
I just felt stiff, tight and stressed.

Now, I’ve finally found that I clenched my jaw and whenever I do it again I actively try to relax.
Even my neck and shoulders can soften now and my hips feel better too (it’s the places where I carry tension a lot). 

Thank you so much!

I have had eating problems and a low self esteem since a child, the last few years I've had a bad relationship with food and making sure I exercised everyday to lose weight, and never really getting anywhere.  I stopped the running and exercise videos to do yoga (to help with my anxieties) and not only did your videos massively help my anxieties and chest pains, I have lost nearly a stone in weight.

YESTERDAY, I came to the mat in the early evening as I had a busy day of house work and then in the afternoon, I had coffee with two new friends and so I was feeling tired but being on this journey, I made sure to switch on to day 14 and do what was possible within my limits and also was challenging for me for the day.

It was really nice to come to the mat and be welcomed with some time to reflect and listen to your innerself and take this journey of today as a way of giving myself a pat on the back for getting so far.  I wouldn't call it a rest day but it was nice to be able to give yourself some rest and to reflect internally.  I got a lot out of the day, mind you when it came to the giving the butt a work out, I was left in awe by what is possible if you continue down the yoga path.  While Adriene was rocking her foot and moving her leg (I thought she was going to rest her leg on her shoulder like she had done previously), I took the time to centre myself and just to calm down and reflect back on the day.  I achieved so much in the day that it was nice to slow it all down and just concentrate on myself.  There was no need to talk, there was no need to think about doing any housework or have chores to be done ... just time to myself ... and it was most rewarding.  

It is nice to know that yoga isn't all about proving or being as flexible as a rubber band, to achieve results and goals, it is so much more and I am truly thankful to have come to day 14 and stayed focused.  Sometimes, you never know what you will feel, find within or discover until you have walked the entire path, not just taken a five minute walk and switched off because it wasn't what you were expecting it to be at the start.  It is all about growing and I am definitely growing and appreciating these lessons.

Thank you Adriene.

PS WHY would anyone hit the unlike button is beyond me
